{"url": "https://www.wikihow.com/Make-a-Top-Knot-Bun", "text": "Article Summary\n\nX\n\nTo make a neat and tidy top knot bun, comb your hair back from your forehead and pull it into a high ponytail, close to the top of your head. Secure the ponytail in place with an elastic hairband. Next, divide the hair into two equal sections. To make them smoother and easier to work with, work a little mousse or styling cream through each of the sections. Grab the sections in both hands and twist them around each other, passing one over the other until the entire length of your ponytail makes one long, twisted section. Take the twisted hair and wrap it clockwise around the elastic at the base of your ponytail. Tuck the end of the hair under the topknot, then pin the knot in place with several bobby pins that match your hair color. Spritz the bun with hairspray to give it extra hold and prevent fly-aways. If you want a messier, more voluminous topknot, back-comb your ponytail before you wrap it. Put your hair into a ponytail like you would for a regular topknot, then divide it into four sections. Grab each section one at a time and hold it straight up, then gently work a comb backwards down the length of the hair to tease it up. When you\u2019re done, use a brush to gently smooth the very top layer of the ponytail, which will make your backcombed hair easier to work with. Take your ponytail and wrap it clockwise around the elastic hairband, then tuck the end of the ponytail under the elastic. Pin your messy bun in place with several bobby pins that match your hair. You can also create a fuller-looking topknot using a hair doughnut. Slide the doughnut over the base of your ponytail, then backcomb your hair like you would for a messy topknot. Wrap your hair clockwise around the doughnut, making sure to cover the doughnut completely. Tuck the end of the ponytail under the doughnut and pin it in place with bobby pins. Spray on some hairspray to help keep your topknot in place. If you want to learn more from our Cosmetologist co-author, like how to use a hair donut to help shape your bun, keep reading!", "images": ["https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/60/Woman-makeup-city.png/-crop-127-140-127px-Woman-makeup-city.png", "https://www.wikihow.com/extensions/wikihow/GreenBox/images/avatar11.png", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/92/Kiss-Step-32-Version-4.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Kiss-Step-32-Version-4.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d7/Scoop-Ice-Cream-Step-3.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Scoop-Ice-Cream-Step-3.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4e/Ashley_Adams_photo.jpeg/-crop-200-200-200px-Ashley_Adams_photo.jpeg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/CommunityAvatar3.png/-crop-104-104-104px-CommunityAvatar3.png", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Christine_George.png/-crop-100-100-95px-Christine_George.png", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/08/Waxing-Crescent-Moon-Meaning-Step-15-Version-2.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Waxing-Crescent-Moon-Meaning-Step-15-Version-2.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/24/Be-Adorable-Step-11-Version-2.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Be-Adorable-Step-11-Version-2.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/extensions/wikihow/GreenBox/images/cta_image_3.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/97/Make-a-Braided-Bun-Step-21.jpg/-crop-342-184-326px-Make-a-Braided-Bun-Step-21.jpg.png", "https://www.wikihow.com/extensions/wikihow/socialstamp/images/icon-pdf.svg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6b/Make-Perfume-Step-31-Version-2.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Make-Perfume-Step-31-Version-2.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a5/Do-a-Curly-Bun-Step-20-Version-8.jpg/-crop-342-184-245px-Do-a-Curly-Bun-Step-20-Version-8.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ae/Quiz-friends-joey-chandler.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Quiz-friends-joey-chandler.jpg", "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ec/Pexels-frostroomhead-14265377.jpg/-crop-127-140-127px-Pexels-frostroomhead-14265377.jpg